A Scotch egg is a boiled egg wrapped in sausage meat, coated in breadcrumbs, and baked or deep-fried. They are eaten as a snack and can make a good appetiser and picnic food. Here are the Ingredients; Preparation Step 1 Pour oil into a large pan and begin preheating on medium-high heat. Step 2 Place about 1 tablespoon of sausage, evenly, around each egg, forming a thin meatball-like layer around the eggs. Step 3 Place breadcrumbs and Â¼ cup parmesan into a shallow dish and gently roll eggs the in mixture until fully coated. Step 4 Fry eggs in two batches, for 5 minutes. Then drain on paper towels and season with salt and pepper. Serve on cocktail or beverage of choice.